Again - what is all too often ignored in moments like this is just how much we have done and continue to do (yes, Republicans too).

Here are just three less than highlighted examples...

UNPRODUCTIVE 
Solutions:
- End the Filibuster
- Illogical & inconsistent gun/magazine grabs
- Attacks on the 2nd Amendment

Rhetoric:
- This party doesn't care
- That party wants to take my guns
- This is what that amendment means

PRODUCTIVE 
Solutions:
- ERPO's
- Close loop holes
- Stronger school safety/policing
- Laws already in place

Rhetoric:
- Communities face challenges beyond even mental health or that which a few million $'s could fix.
- Prayer works. Pray for comfort, wisdom, and healing.

So as you're bombarded with rhetoric and solutions (or silence of those who's narrative an event like this doesn't fit - including my 7 other #GOP opponents), remember which of those are PRODUCTIVE & UNPRODUCTIVE as well as what we're already doing better...
When evil people do evil things the pain we rightfully feel leads to anger - an anger that far too often catalyzes division when it could catalyze change.
